 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-nylz","title":"Real SSH Integration Test Infrastructure","description":"# Real SSH Integration Test Infrastructure

## What
Create a Docker-based SSH testing environment that allows running SSH sync tests
against a real SSH server without requiring external infrastructure.

## Why
The sources module has several untested SSH operations:
- `SyncEngine::sync_source()` - Core sync logic
- `SyncEngine::sync_path_rsync()` - rsync over SSH
- `SyncEngine::get_remote_home()` - Remote ~ expansion
- `expand_tilde_with_home()` - Path normalization

These are currently untested because they require real SSH connectivity.
Using a Docker container gives us a reproducible, isolated test environment.

## Technical Design

### Docker Container Setup
```dockerfile
# tests/docker/Dockerfile.sshd
FROM alpine:latest

RUN apk add --no-cache openssh rsync

# Setup SSH server
RUN ssh-keygen -A
RUN mkdir -p /root/.ssh
RUN echo "PermitRootLogin yes" >> /etc/ssh/sshd_config
RUN echo "PubkeyAuthentication yes" >> /etc/ssh/sshd_config
RUN echo "PasswordAuthentication no" >> /etc/ssh/sshd_config

# Create test directories
RUN mkdir -p /root/.claude/projects/test-project
RUN mkdir -p /root/.codex/sessions
RUN echo '{"type":"user","message":{"content":"test"}}\' > /root/.claude/projects/test-project/session.jsonl

EXPOSE 22

CMD ["/usr/sbin/sshd", "-D", "-e"]
```

### Test Helper Infrastructure
```rust
// tests/ssh_test_helper.rs

use std::process::Command;
use std::time::Duration;
use testcontainers::{Container, Image, GenericImage, clients::Cli};

/// RAII guard that starts/stops the SSH test container
pub struct SshTestServer {
    container: Container<GenericImage>,
    host: String,
    port: u16,
    private_key_path: PathBuf,
}

impl SshTestServer {
    /// Start the SSH test server container
    pub fn start() -> Result<Self, SshTestError> {
        let docker = Cli::default();
        let image = GenericImage::new("cass-ssh-test", "latest")
            .with_exposed_port(22)
            .with_wait_for(testcontainers::WaitFor::message_on_stderr("Server listening"));

        let container = docker.run(image);
        let port = container.get_host_port_ipv4(22);

        // Wait for SSH to be ready
        wait_for_ssh_ready("localhost", port, Duration::from_secs(30))?;

        Ok(Self {
            container,
            host: "localhost".into(),
            port,
            private_key_path: setup_ssh_key()?,
        })
    }

    /// Get SSH connection string for tests
    pub fn ssh_target(&self) -> String {
        format!("root@localhost:{}", self.port)
    }

    /// Get the test data directory on the remote
    pub fn remote_data_dir(&self) -> &str {
        "/root"
    }

    /// Run an SSH command against the test server
    pub fn ssh_exec(&self, cmd: &str) -> Result<String, SshTestError> {
        let output = Command::new("ssh")
            .args(["-p", &self.port.to_string()])
            .args(["-i", self.private_key_path.to_string_lossy().as_ref()])
            .args(["-o", "StrictHostKeyChecking=no"])
            .args(["-o", "UserKnownHostsFile=/dev/null"])
            .arg(&format!("root@{}", self.host))
            .arg(cmd)
            .output()?;

        if !output.status.success() {
            return Err(SshTestError::CommandFailed(
                String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stderr).into()
            ));
        }

        Ok(String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stdout).into())
    }
}

impl Drop for SshTestServer {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        // Container cleanup is automatic via testcontainers
    }
}
```

