## What
Automatically install cass on remote machines that don't have it, via SSH.
Support multiple installation methods with intelligent fallback and robust
handling of long-running installations.

## Why
The biggest friction in multi-machine cass usage is getting cass installed 
everywhere. Users shouldn't have to:
1. SSH to each machine manually
2. Figure out how to install Rust/cargo
3. Wait for cargo install to complete
4. Handle compilation failures

Automating this transforms a 30-minute multi-machine setup into a 5-minute 
guided process.

## Installation Methods (Priority Order)

Selection is automatic based on what's available on the remote:

### 1. Cargo Binstall (Fastest if available)
```bash
cargo binstall --no-confirm coding-agent-search
```
- **When**: cargo-binstall is installed
- **Time**: ~30 seconds
- **Reliability**: High (downloads pre-built binary via cargo)

### 2. Pre-built Binary (Fast, no cargo needed)
```bash
ARCH=$(uname -m)
curl -fsSL "https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/coding_agent_session_search/releases/latest/download/cass-linux-${ARCH}" -o ~/.local/bin/cass
chmod +x ~/.local/bin/cass
```
- **When**: Pre-built binary exists for this arch AND curl/wget available
- **Time**: ~10 seconds
- **Reliability**: Medium (requires release publishing)

### 3. Cargo Install (Most reliable fallback)
```bash
cargo install coding-agent-search
```
- **When**: cargo exists, other methods unavailable/failed
- **Time**: 2-5 minutes (compilation)
- **Reliability**: High (builds from source)

### 4. Full Bootstrap (Last resort)
```bash
# Install rustup
curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh -s -- -y
source ~/.cargo/env
cargo install coding-agent-search
```
- **When**: No cargo, user explicitly confirms
- **Time**: 5-10 minutes
- **Reliability**: High (but changes system)

## Critical: Long-Running Installation Handling

Cargo install can take 5+ minutes. SSH sessions may timeout. Solution:

### Background Execution with Polling
```bash
# Start installation in background with nohup
nohup bash -c 'cargo install coding-agent-search > ~/.cass_install.log 2>&1 && echo DONE >> ~/.cass_install.log' &
INSTALL_PID=$!
echo "INSTALL_PID=$INSTALL_PID"

# Polling script (run separately)
tail -f ~/.cass_install.log | while read line; do
    echo "$line"
    [[ "$line" == "DONE" ]] && break
done
```

### Implementation
```rust
pub struct RemoteInstaller {
    host: String,
    system_info: SystemInfo,
    resources: ResourceInfo,
    local_cass_version: String,  // For version matching
}

pub enum InstallMethod {
    CargoBinstall,
    PrebuiltBinary { url: String, checksum: Option<String> },
    CargoInstall,
    FullBootstrap,  // Includes rustup installation
}

pub struct InstallProgress {
    pub stage: InstallStage,
    pub message: String,
    pub percent: Option<u8>,
}

pub enum InstallStage {
    Preparing,
    Downloading,
    Compiling { crate_name: String },
    Installing,
    Verifying,
    Complete,
    Failed { error: String },
}

impl RemoteInstaller {
    /// Choose best installation method based on system info
    pub fn choose_method(&self) -> InstallMethod {
        if self.system_info.has_cargo_binstall {
            return InstallMethod::CargoBinstall;
        }

        if let Some(url) = self.get_prebuilt_url() {
            return InstallMethod::PrebuiltBinary { url, checksum: None };
        }

        if self.system_info.has_cargo {
            return InstallMethod::CargoInstall;
        }

        InstallMethod::FullBootstrap
    }

    /// Check if resources are sufficient for compilation
    pub fn can_compile(&self) -> Result<(), InstallError> {
        if self.resources.disk_available_mb < 2048 {
            return Err(InstallError::InsufficientDisk {
                available_mb: self.resources.disk_available_mb,
                required_mb: 2048,
            });
        }
        if self.resources.memory_available_mb < 1024 {
            return Err(InstallError::InsufficientMemory {
                available_mb: self.resources.memory_available_mb,
                required_mb: 1024,
            });
        }
        Ok(())
    }

    /// Install cass on remote, streaming progress
    pub async fn install(
        &self,
        on_progress: impl Fn(InstallProgress),
    ) -> Result<InstallResult, InstallError> {
        let method = self.choose_method();

        on_progress(InstallProgress {
            stage: InstallStage::Preparing,
            message: format!("Installing via {:?}", method),
            percent: Some(0),
        });

        match method {
            InstallMethod::CargoBinstall => self.install_via_binstall(on_progress).await,
            InstallMethod::PrebuiltBinary { url, checksum } => {
                self.install_via_binary(&url, checksum.as_deref(), on_progress).await
            }
            InstallMethod::CargoInstall => self.install_via_cargo(on_progress).await,
            InstallMethod::FullBootstrap => self.install_with_bootstrap(on_progress).await,
        }
    }
}
```

