## Error Handling & Recovery

### Missing System Dependencies
If compilation fails with missing headers:
```rust
match detect_missing_deps(&compile_error) {
    Some(MissingDep::OpenSSL) => {
        suggest_fix("Ubuntu/Debian: sudo apt install libssl-dev pkg-config");
        suggest_fix("RHEL/CentOS: sudo yum install openssl-devel");
    }
    Some(MissingDep::BuildEssential) => {
        suggest_fix("Ubuntu/Debian: sudo apt install build-essential");
    }
    // ...
}
```

### Insufficient Resources
```
⚠ Warning: yto has only 512MB RAM available.
  cargo install may fail due to memory constraints.

  Options:
  1. Try anyway (may work for simple crates)
  2. Skip this host
  3. Use pre-built binary (if available)

  Choice [1/2/3]: 
```

### Network Issues
Retry with exponential backoff:
```rust
async fn download_with_retry(url: &str, retries: u32) -> Result<(), Error> {
    for attempt in 0..retries {
        match try_download(url).await {
            Ok(_) => return Ok(()),
            Err(e) if e.is_timeout() => {
                let delay = Duration::from_secs(2u64.pow(attempt));
                sleep(delay).await;
            }
            Err(e) => return Err(e),
        }
    }
    Err(Error::MaxRetriesExceeded)
}
```

## Security Considerations
- Only download from trusted sources (GitHub releases, crates.io)
- Verify checksums for binary downloads when available
- Show exact commands before execution
- User must explicitly confirm installation
- Never use `curl | bash` without showing the script content first
- Log all installation commands for audit

